**IOC** means Inversion of Control and this is a priciple.
It controll object creation instead of the programmer.
OR
Spring Framework manages **object creation** and **lifecycle**.
client <-> controller , service , Repository <-> Database.

**DI** Dependency Injection is actual implementation of IOC.
This is a Design pattern.
Four techniques to archieve DI:-
1.Without DI
2.Constructor Injection
3.Field Injection
4.Setter Injection


**Important Annotations**
Annotation	Use
@Component	Create bean/object
@Autowired	Inject dependency
@Service	  Service layer bean
@Repository	Database layer bean
@Controller	Controller bean



